name: ONE OF A KIND
desc: On the fifth and sixth floor of a new building on Frishman street, this duplex penthouse offers you the best place to be in Tel-Aviv. Getting in, on the lower floor of that stunning flat, you will find the bedrooms including 2 with ensuite bathroom and a guest toilet, in addition a large leaving and a sunny balcony. On the second floor, you will find the kitchen, the dining area, and the roof top terrace. The roof top terrace is a piece by himself. Indeed totally furnished with a large dining table (up to 10 guests), an outdoor leaving room with sofa and a Jacuzzi. (hot tub) facing the ocean, the all surrounded by a spectacular vegetation.

reviews.txt: Very good location minutes from the beach. House is furnished to a high standard, very clean with well equipped kitchen. Washer & dryer on premises. Amazing roof terrace with jacuzzi and BBQ and partial sea view. Host checked in regularly to ensure everything went well. Two downsides: 1) there are three bedrooms and the two showers are in two of the bedrooms. So people in 3rd bedroom have to go into other peoples rooms to shower (there is a hallway toilet however) and 2) the third bedroom has no windows. If you don’t think those things will bother you I can highly recommend it!
I‘ve seen many places in Tel Aviv. This is the Nr. 1 Hot. Hot. Hot.
Wonderful place, wonderful people, will absolutely stay again!

reviews.txt: The host canceled this reservation 3 days before arrival. This is an automated posting.

Great apartment, small but great use of space. Really great shower. Nespresso coffee maker (I like coffee) but you'll need to bring your own coffee pods. Very comfortable bed. Great neighborhood, great location, interesting, close to everything, in the heart of Central district, lots of restaurants, but is noisy late at night --great, if you're into a loud bar scene. It's a 5-floor walk-up and no lift, but the apartment is worth it. Very good value. Get good directions --unless you know your way around it can be difficult to find and the building's not well-marked.
Wonderful place, wonderful people, will absolutely stay again!
